CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 18, 1962, page 14, reads: "Policy - Makers - This group constitutes the policy making staff of the Pennsylvania Baptist Congress of Christian Education. This is, in fact, the executive board. This board makes the policy and approves the program. in front row are (left to right) Miss C. Ross, corresponding secretary; W. M. Stockton, vice president; Mrs. V. Valentine, recording secretary; Eustace Gay, president; Mrs. E. Venable, statistician; W. Williams, vice president at large; D. A. Delaver, assistant dean, and W. A. Arvin, dean. Other leaders, members of this board, include the district deans and directors, and others."
TitMainTitle: Men and women, including some wearing ribbons on lapels, seated in pews of Mt. Zion Baptist Church
